In this statement, President Barack Obama reflects on the one-year anniversary of the earthquake in Haiti. He pays tribute to the lives lost and acknowledges the efforts made by Americans and people from around the world in providing humanitarian aid. He mentions the ongoing support and assistance provided by the United States in helping Haiti recover and rebuild, including responding to additional challenges such as the outbreak of cholera and Hurricane Tomas. While progress has been made, there are still challenges to overcome, such as the amount of rubble and the number of people living in tents. President Obama emphasizes that Haiti should take the lead in its own recovery, with the international community fulfilling their pledges to support the long-term effort. He reassures that the United States will continue to be a partner in Haiti's rebuilding process.